Class Description
App
This class is the entry point to start the Social Magnet application.

This Class represents the City Farmers page
Crop
This Class represents the crop in the City Farmers Game
CropController
This Class represents the CropController class that contains the method to determine the yield of a crop
CropDAO
This Class represents the Crop DAO.
DBController
This Class represents Database Controller which prepares the connection between the Database and the Application
Farmer
This Class represents the farmer in the City Farmers Game
FarmerController
This Class represents the FarmerController class that contains the methods representing the actions that the farmer can perform

This Class represents the Farmer DAO.

MainMenuPage
This Class represents the Main Menu page of the Social Magnet.
Member
This Class represents the member in Social Magnet
MemberController
This Class represents the MemberController that contains methods related to the Member class such as registering, login, showing a member's list of friends and friend requests, and creating a friend request.
MemberDAO
This Class represents the Member DAO.
MyFriendsPage
This Class represents the My Friends page of the Social Magnet
MyWallPage

NewsFeedPage
This Class represents the News Feed page of Social Magnet
Page

Post
This Class represents the post in Social Magnet
PostController
This Class represents the PostController class that contains the methods related to the Post class.
PostDAO
This Class represents the Post DAO.
Reply

Session
This Class represents the Session class.
Store
This Class represents the crop in the City Farmers Game
StoreController
This Class represents the StoreController that contains methods related to the Store class.
StorePage
This Class represents the Store page of City Farmers game
Text
This Class represents text that can be posted onto the Social Magnet.
ThreadPage
This Class represents the Thread page of Social Magnet
VisitPage
This Class represents the Visit page
WelcomePage
This Class represents the Welcome page, which is shown to the user when he or she first starts the application.
